org.hkijena.acaq5.api.algorithm

Class ACAQMultiDataInterface

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hkijena.acaq5.api.algorithm.ACAQMultiDataInterface

  • public class ACAQMultiDataInterface
extends Object
    Groups inputs together based on annotations. This is a weaker variant of ACAQDataInterface. Unlike ACAQDataInterface, this class does not assume uniqueness.

        public ACAQMultiDataInterface(ACAQAlgorithm algorithm,
                              List<ACAQDataSlot> inputSlots,
                              Set<ACAQTraitDeclaration> referenceTraits,
                              int row)
        Creates a new interface
        Parameters:
        algorithm - The algorithm
        inputSlots - Input slots that are considered during the calculation. The first one is used as reference
        referenceTraits - Annotation types considered as reference. If empty, all traits are used as reference
        row - the row this data interface is generated for
